6 An Act relating to wildlife; amending 29 O.S. 2021,
Section 4-114, as amended by Section 6, Chapter 6,
7 O.S.L. 2024 (29 O.S. Supp. 2025, Section 4-114),
which relates to hunting and fishing licenses;
8 increasing required term of residency for certain
license; updating statutory language; updating
9 statutory reference; authorizing certain license
upgrade; authorizing velvet buck controlled hunt;
10 defining terms; setting controlled hunt, bag, and tag
limits; specifying means of take; applying velvet
11 buck harvest to deer bag limits; directing the
Oklahoma Wildlife Conservation Commission to
12 promulgate rules; authorizing cancellation for
certain conditions; prohibiting certain refunds of
13 fees; requiring valid license, permit, and stamp;
providing for enforcement of laws and rules; setting
14 licenses, permits, or stamps by rule; requiring
controlled hunt to be based on normal deer
15 populations; providing for codification; and
providing an effective date.
16
17
18 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
19 SECTION 1. AMENDATORY 29 O.S. 2021, Section 4-114, as
20 amended by Section 6, Chapter 6, O.S.L. 2024 (29 O.S. Supp. 2025,
21 Section 4-114), is amended to read as follows:
22 Section 4-114. A. All legal residents who have resided in the
23 state for at least six (6) months one (1) year and intend to remain
24 residents may purchase lifetime fishing licenses or lifetime
