1 comb ination hunting and fishing licenses from the State Wildlife
2 Conservation Director.
3 B. The fee for these licenses shall be:
4 1. Lifetime fishing license, Three Hundred Seventy-five Dollars
5 ($375.00);
6 2. Lifetime combination hunting and fishing license, One
7 Thousand Twenty-four Dollars ($1,024.00);
8 3. Senior citizen lifetime fishing license for persons sixty-
9 five (65) years of age or older, Thirty Dollars ($30.00); and
10 4. Senior citizen lifetime combination hunting and fishing
11 license for persons sixty-five (65) years of age or older, Sixty
12 Dollars ($60.00).
13 C. Legal A legal resident having proper certification from the
14 United States Department of Veterans Affairs or its successor
15 certifying that the person is a disabled veteran and registered with
16 the veterans registry created by the Oklahoma Department of Veterans
17 Affairs may purchase a disability lifetime combination hunting and
18 fishing license from the State Wildlife Conservation Director. The
19 fees for the license shall be as follows:
20 1. Two Hundred Dollars ($200.00) for veterans having a
21 disability of less than sixty percent (60%); and
22 2. Twenty-five Dollars ($25.00) for veterans having a
23 disability of sixty percent (60%) or more.
24
